so I can heat up the tang
without any of that heat

20:22.722 --> 20:25.141
<i>going into</i>
<i>the heat-treated blade.</i>

20:25.141 --> 20:28.185
- I love the wet towel.
I mean, it's such a smart idea.

20:28.185 --> 20:29.895
He doesn't have to quench it.

20:29.895 --> 20:31.230
He's going to the anvil.
You go man.

20:31.230 --> 20:33.733
- He's going in.
- You go.

20:33.733 --> 20:36.569
- How often have we said,
"Look, there's a big issue

20:36.569 --> 20:38.529
with this blade;

20:38.529 --> 20:40.114
it's this," and the smith's
never addressed it?

20:40.114 --> 20:41.699
- Yeah, like, la,
la, la, la, la.

20:41.699 --> 20:42.742
- He's tak--yeah,
he's taking care of it

20:42.742 --> 20:44.994
in the first 12 minutes.

20:44.994 --> 20:45.953
- I'm able to straighten it out
and actually get it going back

20:45.953 --> 20:47.538
<i>in the right direction.</i>

20:47.538 --> 20:49.039
I'm thrilled.
This is gonna work.

20:49.039 --> 20:52.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:52.668 --> 20:55.254
- Ooh, it's so much quieter.
- Yeah.

20:55.254 --> 20:57.715
Give it about two seconds.

20:57.715 --> 21:01.177
- My plan for this round
is to get my bevels put in,

21:01.177 --> 21:03.220
and I need to get my tang
thinned down a little bit

21:03.220 --> 21:05.347
'cause she was thick.

